Short Deskription of Prelude_info_mixer.

Prelude info_mixer is a tool to control the settings of the prelude soundcard.
You can set the loudness of the Line, AUX1 , AUX2 , Mono and Loopback input.
You can set the Right and left  loudness separate.
If you will set both (right and left) to the same level, you set the right value
and then you click to the Button ( Line, AUX1, AUX2 ) .The program sets then 
the left value to the same as the right is.
For the DAC ( output ) and GAIN there is the same function.

The checkbox button Filter sets the ADC filter on/of  and the checkbox 
gadgets Rmic and Lmic sets the MicGain +20db on or of.
The toggle button Input sets the channel with is routed to the ADC ,
the toggle button frequency sets the frequency of the Sample.

The program saves automatic at program end the actual settings to ENV.
The menu Save ENVARC saves the actual settings to ENVARC:
The menu load loads the ENV settings and sets it as actual values.
The menue Set default loads the ENVARC: settings and sets it as actual values.
The menu Update data sets the actual values to the GUI 
( Update if other programs have changed the values)
Reset Card resets the Prelude Soundcard.
Card Info gives the user a info witch process is running ( Play, Rec use of the card ).

Have a nice day
